list.item:
                  The Maxim, Quod efficit tale, est magis tale; or Propter
quod unumquodque tale, ipsum magis tale;
or Constituens constituto potior, is examined, 200.

div.p:
THE Holy Fathers and Martyrs in the prior and
purer Age of the Church knew no other Doctrine;
they spake no other Language.

Athanasius his Suffrage and Testimony you have before, cap. 5. and with him you have Hosius in epist. ad Solit. vit. agent. writing and averring constantly, confidently, to Constantius an Arrian Emperour, 〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 ; God hath given to thee the
Kingdom, the Sovereignty. If you will have Athanasius alone, take his Testimony from his own Mouth, in his Apology to Constantius;
〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 ; But thanks to the Lord who gave to thee the Empire.
